# Copy to deploy/.env and adjust.
#
# Pick ONE of the two scenarios below.

# ============================================================
# Scenario 1 — Prometheus + Grafana only (default profile).
#
# Exporters run elsewhere (on each SAN host, or anywhere reachable).
# One or more SANsymphony groups, each pointing at its own
# ssv-prom-exporter instance. Format: "groupname=host:port,...".
# The groupname becomes the `group` Prometheus label used by the
# Grafana dashboards to filter / split between groups.
#
#   docker compose up -d
# ============================================================
EXPORTER_TARGETS=LAB-PVE=10.12.110.11:9876
# EXPORTER_TARGETS=LAB-PVE=10.12.110.11:9876,PROD=10.0.0.5:9876

# ============================================================
# Scenario 2 — Full stack: Prometheus + Grafana + exporter
# (compose profile `full`).
#
# The exporter ALSO runs as a service in this compose stack and
# scrapes one SANsymphony group via its REST API. Leave
# EXPORTER_TARGETS empty above (or omit it) to use the auto-generated
# `<SSV_GROUP>=exporter:9876` target.
#
#   docker compose --profile full up -d --build
# ============================================================
# SSV_URL=https://10.0.0.1
# SSV_USER=administrator
# SSV_PASS=ChangeMe!
# SSV_GROUP=lab                   # becomes the `group` Prometheus label
# SSV_BASES=10.0.0.2,10.0.0.3     # optional cold-start backup IPs
# SSV_BACKUP_CIDRS=10.0.0.0/24    # optional CIDR allowlist for discovered backups
# EXPORTER_IMAGE=ghcr.io/lblanc/ssv-prom-exporter:latest

# Grafana admin password (anonymous viewer is always on, this gates editing).
GF_ADMIN_PASSWORD=admin
